<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>su.kidoz.storage_wiper</id>

  <name>Storage Wiper</name>
  <summary>Securely wipe storage devices with DoD-compliant algorithms</summary>

  <metadata_license>MIT</metadata_license>
  <project_license>MIT</project_license>

  <description>
    <p>
      Storage Wiper is a secure disk wiping tool with a modern GTK4/libadwaita
      interface. It provides multiple DoD-compliant algorithms for permanent
      data destruction on storage devices.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>8 secure wipe algorithms including DoD 5220.22-M, Gutmann, and GOST</li>
      <li>Support for HDDs, SSDs, NVMe, and USB drives</li>
      <li>ATA Secure Erase for SSDs with hardware support</li>
      <li>Real-time progress tracking with pass-level details</li>
      <li>Automatic SSD detection with algorithm recommendations</li>
      <li>Privilege separation via D-Bus and Polkit for security</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This is a defensive security tool for proper data sanitization when
      decommissioning storage devices, preparing drives for resale, or ensuring
      data privacy.
    </p>
  </description>

